openUI
for more details, please read my blog at http://albert.-david.blogspot.com/

openUI - This term refers to both h/w and its control software,
hardware: This is tiny USB hardware based on atmel attiny2313, acting as a user interface to the headless linux box.
          Headless means, A Linux box without any user I/O interface(like keyboard and display).
software: openUI hardware needs a control daemon running on the linux host, this daemon uses libusb library
          functions to communicate with openUI hardware over USB bus.